<HEAD>Former SMU president Willis Tate Dead at 77</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Tate </PERSON>, who served as president of <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Methodist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> for nearly 20 years, died of an apparent heart attack while on a trip with his wife in <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION>, the school announced Monday. He was 77. <PERSON> Tate </PERSON>, who died Sunday night, was the university's president from 1954 to 1971 and again from July 1974 to October 1975. He retired as chancellor in 1976 and since then had served as president emeritus of <ORGANIZATION> SMU </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Tate </PERSON> was an all-conference tackle and an honorable mention All-American in 1931, when <ORGANIZATION> SMU </ORGANIZATION> won the <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> football championship. He received his bachelor degree of arts in 1932 and his master's of arts in sociology in 1935, both from <ORGANIZATION> SMU </ORGANIZATION> After serving as teacher and school principal in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Tate </PERSON> returned to <ORGANIZATION> SMU </ORGANIZATION> in 1945 as assistant dean of students. `` He will be remembered as the protector of academic freedom during the difficult times in the 1950s and 1960s and as a strong supporter of curriculum reforms,'' said <ORGANIZATION> SMU </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Pye </PERSON>. <PERSON> Tate </PERSON> also presided over the establishment of <ORGANIZATION> SMU </ORGANIZATION>'s School of the Arts and the launching of doctoral programs on campus. He and his wife, the late <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> <PERSON> Estes </PERSON> <PERSON> Tate </PERSON>, had two children. Tate is survived by <PERSON> Marian </PERSON> <PERSON> Cleary </PERSON> <PERSON> Tate </PERSON>, whom he married in 1988, his two children and three grandchildren.
