<HEAD>Top Mexican Politician Killed In Car Crash</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto M04</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ISAAC A. LEVI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Clouthier </PERSON>, who as a candidate in the 1988 presidential election brought conservative ideas back to Mexican politics, died in an auto accident in his native <LOCATION> Sinaloa </LOCATION> state. He was 55. Thousands of supporters marched through the streets of the state capital, <LOCATION> Culiacan </LOCATION>, late Sunday carrying the blue-and-white flags of his <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Action </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> with a black-bow ribbon sewed on one corner as a sign of mourning. In <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, about 200 supporters gathered around the Angel of Independence monument holding signs that read, `` Thank you, Maquio,'' <PERSON> Clouthier </PERSON>'s nickname. <PERSON> Clouthier </PERSON> and political colleague <PERSON> Javier </PERSON> <PERSON> Calvo </PERSON> <PERSON> Manriquez </PERSON> died Sunday when the car they were in crashed head on into a truck loaded with papayas, police said. The accident occurred halfway between <LOCATION> Culiacan </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> beach resort of <LOCATION> Mazatlan </LOCATION>. A police news bulletin said the driver of the truck, <PERSON> Aurelio </PERSON> <PERSON> Flores </PERSON> <PERSON> Gomez </PERSON>, was detained for questioning. When he died, <PERSON> Clouthier </PERSON> was stumping the state to help <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Action </ORGANIZATION> mayoral candidates running in Oct. 15 balloting. Friends, political foes and former business associates mourned the burly, white-bearded politician who finished third in <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s 1988 election, which was won by President <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Salinas </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Gortari </PERSON> and marred by fraud <PERSON> Salinas </PERSON>, on a one-week visit to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOC