. The list of unindicted co-conspirators was included in a pretrial motion filed by one of Mrs. <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON>' co-defendants, <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Overseas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>. The actor, known for his perpetual tan and for his portrayal of a vampire in the movie `` Love at First Bite,'' has denied rumors that he and Mrs. <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> were romantically linked. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON>'s name previously has come up in connection with legal action against the Marcoses, specifically, in a lawsuit by the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION> government against the Marcoses. <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bersin </PERSON>, an attorney for the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>, said the suit alleges that the Marcoses invested in a <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> house owned by <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON>. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> has said he has done nothing wrong. In March 1986, <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> said through his attorney, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Sherman </PERSON>, that <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> had no financial involvement in the estate. <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> bought the estate, once owned by <PERSON> Charlie </PERSON> <PERSON> Chaplin </PERSON>, for $ 1.2 million in 1981. The deal was financed by <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON>'s own money, <ORGANIZATION> Wells </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fargo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> and the seller, <PERSON> Sherman </PERSON> said. In late 1983, <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> used the increased value of the property to get a five-year loan from <ORGANIZATION> Calno </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> N.V. </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> Netherlands </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antilles </LOCATION>. Calno reportedly has ties with the <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> family.
