<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Jury selection got under way today in the liability trial in the 1987 <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> crash that killed 156 people, with lawyers prepared to battle over who is to blame for the tragic outcome of Flight 255. The trial before District Judge <PERSON> Julian </PERSON> <PERSON> Cook </PERSON>, expected to take four to six months, will feature about 4,000 exhibits, including shredded plane parts and hundreds of photographs. At issue is whether <LOCATION> Northwest </LOCATION> or the maker of the MD-80 plane, <ORGANIZATION> McDonnell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Douglas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, or both, are liable in the fiery Aug. 16, 1987, crash. `` Expect a major battle between <ORGANIZATION> McDonnell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Douglas </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION>, trying to blame it on each other,'' said <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Schaden </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Birmingham </LOCATION>, one of five attorneys serving on a steering committee representing about 100 plaintiffs. `` It's such a hotly contested liability issue. Neither one will admit liability, and that's rare,'' <PERSON> Schaden </PERSON> said. A <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> report on the crash near <LOCATION> Detroit </LOCATION> Metropolitan Airport said the pilots failed to properly set the wing flaps and slats before takeoff. The Phoenix-bound plane, never able to gain altitude, slammed into an Interstate 94 entrance ramp, killing 154 people on board and two people on the ground. The sole plane survivor was <PERSON> Cecelia </PERSON> <PERSON> Cichan </PERSON>, then 4, who lost her parents and brother and now lives with relatives in <LOCATION> Alabama </LOCATION>. Some relatives of crash victims said they would be at court every day. <PE