<HEAD>Cosby Daughter Treated for Drug, Alcohol Habit</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS penultimate graf with 3 grafs to UPDATE with further from
Cosby spokesman. Picks up last graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LANTANA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Entertainer <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON> used the `` tough love'' approach with his 23-year-old daughter, <PERSON> Erinn </PERSON>, when she told him that she was addicted to drugs and alcohol, both father and daughter say. <PERSON> Erinn </PERSON> <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON>, who checked out of a drug rehabilitation center Sept. 24, said she began using cocaine at age 19, but that her parents had no idea se had a drug habit until she wrote them a letter six months ago. She said she had kicked a $ 200-a-day cocaine habit by then but was still heavily hooked on pot and alcohol. <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON>, who plays a father-knows-best-style dad on his hit television series and wrote a best-seller `` Fatherhood'' about his experiences with his five children, said he consulted specialists on how to handle the situation and he and his wife wrote back urging her to seek treatment. But they refused to coddle her. `` ` Tough love' is the only way of dealing with this. We love her and want her to get better, but we have to take a very firm, very tough stand that forces her to realize that no one can fix things for her,'' the star told the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enquirer </ORGANIZATION>. `` She has to beat this on her own.'' `` People see <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON> as a super dad. But I'm proof that drug and alcohol tragedies can happen even in the most loving families,'' said his daughter, who is staying with a cousin in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> after her five-week stay at <LOCATION> Edgehill </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Newport </LOCATION> hospital in <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Brokaw </PERSON>, <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON>'s <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles-based </LOCATION> spokesman, confirmed today that Ms. <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON> is under treatment for a drug and alcohol problem, and said <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON> would have no further comment other than what he had told the Enquirer. The Enquirer piece is `` the only interview that he's been willing to give on the matter,'' <PERSON> Brokaw </PERSON> said. `` He has a relationship with them. He has found them to treat him fairly.'' He said he could n't confirm any of what Ms. <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON> is quoted as saying except that she did have a substance abuse problem. Ms. <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON>, the second of <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON>'s five children, told the Lantana-based newspaper she began drinking and smoking marijuana about age 14 while at boarding school.
