<HEAD>Kasparov Wins Dutch Tournament</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TILBURG, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 World chess champion <PERSON> Garri </PERSON> <PERSON> Kasparov </PERSON> of the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> won the 13th annual <ORGANIZATION> Interpolis </ORGANIZATION> chess tournament Monday with a record score of 12 points in 14 matches. <PERSON> Viktor </PERSON> <PERSON> Korchnoi </PERSON>, a Soviet exile who lives in <LOCATION> Switzerland </LOCATION>, finished second. First prize in the $ 50,000 event was $ 12,000. <PERSON> Kasparov </PERSON>'s performance in this southern Dutch city also gave him to 2,795 points for the year on the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chess </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Federation </ORGANIZATION>'s international ranking list, surpassing the record 2,785 earned by former champion <PERSON> Bobby </PERSON> <PERSON> Fischer </PERSON> in 1972 The win at <LOCATION> Tilburg </LOCATION>, where the maximum possible score was 14, extends an undefeated string for the 26-year-old Soviet grandmaster that began in 1981. He does not plan to enter any more tournaments this year. <PERSON> Korchnoi </PERSON>, 58, compiled 8 -LCB- points in the tournament and won $ 8,000 for his second-place finish.
