know how the board members could not be aware of the financial crisis at <ORGANIZATION> Heritage </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> USA </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON> testified. `` They knew we had cash flow problems and they voted to borrow funds to pay for them.'' Ms. <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> asked <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON> if he was contradicting testimony from six board members who said they did n't know about the ministry's financial problems `` I would tell them we were in great financial need. They were always up to date on all the financial information,'' <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON> said. `` I gave them the information to the best of my ability.'' But <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON> later acknowledged he may have painted a rosy picture of <ORGANIZATION> PTL </ORGANIZATION>'s finances to fellow board members. `` I was a minister,'' he said. `` I did my best to keep them informed and I know I was positive in the face of turmoil at times. I preached faith.''
