<HEAD>Coal Output Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic coal production totaled 19.9 million short tons during the week ended Sept. 23, up slightly from the 19.6 million short tons produced the previous week, the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> reported Monday. The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> coal industry produced 19.3 million short tons in the same week last year, according to the department's <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Information </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>. Domestic coal production so far this year is 699.9 million short tons, 5.9 percent above last year's production at this time, the agency said. The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
