<HEAD>USX Puts Oil Reserves on Block</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said today it is offering to sell the oil and natural gas reserves of its <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Gas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> subsidiary. The oil and steel giant said it has retained the investment banking firm <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> to handle the sale. The reserves are mainly located in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Oklahoma </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Arkansas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>, issued 133 million shares of stock in 1986 to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Gas in a deal valued at around $ 3 billion. <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> has been disappointed by the company's earnings ever since. The parent has pinned its hopes for a turnaround at <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Gas on the prospect of natural gas prices surging. A sale is anticipated by year's end, said <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Keslar </PERSON>, who declined to say what value <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> places on the reserves. <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Gas has 1.2 trillion cubic feet of gas in reserve, about a quarter of the 3.5 trillion cubic feet held by the other <ORGANIZATION> USX </OR