<HEAD>Unions File Racketeering Countersuit Against Texas Air, Eastern</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: SUBS 3rd graf to UPDATE with attorney's confirmation that countersuit
filed; picks up 4th graf pvs bg'ng, The action, ...; NEW grafs 7-10 to
UPDATE with judge enjoining union suit against Eastern leasing planes from
Continental, edit to conform; picks up 8th graf pvs bg'ng, The lawsuit
...</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Striking <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> pilots and Machinists unions said Monday they filed a civil racketeering lawsuit against <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, company chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> and two subsidiary airlines. The lawsuit seeks relief for damages to employees and shareholders from a pattern of `` fraudulent empire-building, misrepresentation, extortion, asset-stripping and criminal activity against <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> unions,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Line </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pilots </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> said. A spokesman for the clerk's office at the federal court in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> was unable to confirm receipt of the documents on Monday afternoon, but <ORGANIZATION> ALPA </ORGANIZATION> attorney <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Harwood </PERSON> confirmed that he had filed the papers. The action, a counterclaim to an earlier lawsuit filed by <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>, charges violations of the federal Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act by the company. <ORGANIZATION> ALPA </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Cole </PERSON> said many of the allegations have been made to the bankruptcy court in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, but the racketeering complaint was filed because the progress of the bankruptcy case has been slow. Eastern spokesman <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Mattell </PERSON> said the lawsuit was without merit. In a separate action Monday, a federal bankruptcy judge in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> granted an injunction to Eastern blocking another union lawsuit from being tried in the <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> district court. That suit, filed by <ORGANIZATION> ALPA </ORGANIZATION> alone on Sept. 1, challenges <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s recent practice of leasing DC-9 jets and flight crews from sister carrier <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>. In a hearing before <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> ALPA </ORGANIZATION> attorney <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Simon </PERSON> contended that Eastern violated its collective bargaining agreement with the pilots union by leasing the planes and crews from Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Zirinsky </PERSON>, a lawyer for Eastern, insisted that the leasing arrangement did n't violate any labor agreements and was vital to <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s rebuilding effort. <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON> agreed, saying that the loss of the leasing arrangement _ now involving 16 jets and crews _ could cause `` irreparable harm'' to Eastern. In the corruption countersuit, the unions alleged a pattern of racketeering activity in violation of the securities laws, mail and wire fraud statutes and other federal laws. In addition to <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>, the lawsuit names subsidiary <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Jet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. The lawsuit seeks multimillion-dollar damages and relief to be determined by the court. The civil RICO statute allows juries to award triple damages. Because Eastern is in bankruptcy proceedings in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, the unions said they will ask for a release from the bankruptcy court to press the claims against <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> filed a civil RICO lawsuit against <ORGANIZATION> ALPA </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machinists </ORGANIZATION> in May 1988 accusing Eastern unions of trying to wreck the airline in order to force its sale at a loss. Eastern's Machinists, pilots and flight attendants walked off the job last March 4 and <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> filed for bankruptcy protection from creditors five days later.
