<HEAD>French Arms Exports Rose 30 Percent in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The value of export orders booked by French arms manufacturers surged by 30 percent last year to $ 6 billion, the <ORGANIZATION> French </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> said Monday. The ministry said 53 percent of the total was accounted for by orders for aeronautical equipment and 36 percent for land-based defense equipment, while naval orders represented 11 percent. <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>'s biggest customers remain the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, together accounting for 55 percent of total orders. <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> account for 24 percent of the 1988 total, and <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> for 14 percent.
