<HEAD>EDS: to UPDATE with company comment on possibility voluntary severance
will not bring sufficient workforce reductions, INSERTS one new graf after
3rd graf; pickup 4th graf pvs: The company. SUBS 8th graf pvs to ADD Fort
Worth, Texas, to list of cities where severance offer expected; Pickup
last graf: Motorola, headquartered ...</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SCHAUMBURG, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> announced Monday a plan to reduce its 105,000-employee workforce by some 2,500 people through a program emphasizing what the electronics company called `` enhanced voluntary severance.'' `` This is aimed primarily at salaried employees,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Chuck </PERSON> <PERSON> Sengstock </PERSON>. `` We've improved our normal voluntary severance package. Those applying who are accepted will now receive two weeks' severance pay for each year of service.'' The program, which is restricted primarily to <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> operations, goes into effect immediately, <PERSON> Sengstock </PERSON> said. He said most of those being urged to take the severance package work in the company's communications and semiconductor products groups. `` If we do not have enough people volunteering for severance, some involuntary severances may occur, but we wo n't know about that for at least six weeks,'' said <PERSON> Sengstock </PERSON>. `` We're hoping we can meet our goals through voluntary severance, normal attrition and internal business transfers.'' The company said a pretax provision of approximately $ 43 million to cover the cost of the severance would be reflected in third-quarter earnings to be announced next week. `` We retain our confidence in the company's growth prospects,'' said company president <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Fisher </PERSON>. `` This program simply reflects what we at <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> consider to be good and prudent management and provides a means for us to reduce our cost base through a voluntary process which is in the best interest of our employees.'' The package will be offered to workers at selected <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> facilities until approximately mid-November, <PERSON> Sengstock </PERSON> said. He mentioned plants in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Austin </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lauderdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>; and <LOCATION> Boynton </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, as among the facilities where salaried employees would be encouraged to take severance. <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION>, headquartered in this <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> suburb, has plants or other facilities at some 24 locations in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Sengstock </PERSON> said.
